  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 13 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1090 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch pieces (peel first if desired). Core, deseed, and cut @poblano pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Thinly slice @jalapeño{1} into rounds, removing ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Quarter and peel @red onion{1}; thinly slice one quarter (two quarters for 4 servings; save the rest for another use). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves and stems. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (quarter both limes for 4).

Toss sweet potatoes and poblano on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{3%teaspoon} (divide between 2 sheets for 4 servings). Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, and half the @cumin{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{½%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Stir in onion and jalapeño; cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Remove plastic wrap and set mixture aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pineapple, garlic, lime zest, remaining cumin, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring, until pineapple is browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

In a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{6%tablespoon} and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste; season with salt. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide roasted veggies, pineapple salsa, pickled veggies, and crema between tortillas. Garnish with cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> In this veggie twist on tacos al pastor, pork is swapped out for roasted, cumin-and-oregano-spiced sweet potato and poblano. Once the veggies are tender and lightly charred, they're piled into steamy tortillas along with pickled onion and jalapeño, warm pineapple salsa, hot sauce crema, and a sprinkle of cilantro. Yep, Tuesday (any day) just got a whole lot better.